org.matsim.core.mobsim.qsim.interfaces

Interface MobsimEngine

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Steppable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NetworkChangeEventsEngineI, TeleportationEngine
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActivityEngine, DefaultTeleportationEngine, NetworkChangeEventsEngine, QNetsimEngine, TransitQSimEngine, WithinDayEngine

    public interface MobsimEngine
extends Steppable
    Design thoughs:
    • This is an engine that is plugged into the Mobsim. Thus the name.
    • The main difference between a MobsimEngine and, say, a MobsimBeforeSimStepListener, is that the MobsimEngine obtains the InternalInterface, whose main functionality is arrangeNextAgentState, i.e. it allows to move the agents forward.
    Author:
    dgrether, nagel
